oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo postcard of Prentiss Arthur Cogswell and wife
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: A studio portrait photograph showing Prentiss Arthur Cogswell and his French war bride, Germain Gireud, on their wedding day. The two met in Grenoble, France while he was serving with a mechanical unit. The army would not allow Germaine to travel with the troops so she came over several weeks later on a different ship. Cogswell was originally from Illinois but moved to Memphis around 1923. He worked for Goodyear Rubber Company as an accountant. His uniform is housed at the Tenn. State Museum.
